# Architecture

Server-authoritative **modular monolith**: one deployable app, clean internal packages.

```text
/apps/web        SvelteKit UI + server routes/actions
/packages/domain pure game rules (survey, thumpers, crafting, economy math)
/packages/db     Drizzle schema, migrations, typed queries
/packages/jobs   Postgres-backed workers / scheduled tasks
/packages/shared shared types and utilities
```

## Separation rules

- **Domain package** holds game logic with no Svelte, HTTP, or DB driver imports.
- **DB package** owns schema and persistence; domain receives/returns plain types.
- **Web app** validates input (Zod/Valibot), calls domain functions, writes transactionally.
- UI components display state and submit actions; they do not embed economy formulas.

## Action flow pattern

```text
Client form/action → validate → domain function → DB transaction → response
```

## Testing priority

Vitest on domain invariants first (inventory never negative, idempotent claims, crafting consumes exact inputs). Playwright only for one or two critical UI flows.

## Growth path

Extract a standalone API (Fastify/Hono) only if SvelteKit server routes become unwieldy. Do not start with microservices.
